Reasoning: The paper deals with constructing a category of polynomial endofunctors and simulation cells, which is reminiscent of Day's convolution on presheaves. This suggests that the paper may belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) or Category Theory (cs.CT). Additionally, the paper defines an additive and exponential structure, which is a common theme in Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of universal properties without reference to representing polynomial diagrams suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
